#: Game.Levels.DSL_Knights_Knaves.L12_31
msgid "\n"
"§0 means that there are no knights or there are two or more knights.\n"
"\n"
"Since we know that §1 are knaves then it is the former, i.e. there are no knights. This means that §2 is a knave.\n"
"\n"
"To obtain this result:\n"
"- First start by unfolding §3.\n"
"- Use §4 given what you know to simplify the obtained expression after unfolding.\n"
"- The final answer after simplification would be that §5 is a knave.\n"
"\n"
"After obtaining that §6 is a knave, we now know that everyone is a knave but we also know that §7 and so a contradiction.\n"
"\n"
"To obtain this contradiction, §8 then simplify the unfolded expression or construct a proof of §9.\n"
""
msgstr ""

