#: Game.Levels.Logic.L04_Implication
msgid "In this level, we introduce the logical implication §0 connective.\n"
"Logical implication §1 is made up of two components:\n"
"- The premise, which in this case is §2\n"
"- The conclusion, which in this case is §3\n"
"\n"
"§4 is read as 'If §5 is true, then §6 is true'.\n"
"§7 being true IMPLIES §8 being true. A proof of §9 IMPLIES a proof of §10.\n"
"\n"
"In the current proof state, we know §11 and we know §12. Therefore, we can conclude §13.\n"
"\n"
"You can think of logical implication as a function. §14 takes a proof of §15 and returns a proof of §16.\n"
"\n"
"Pass §17 as an argument to §18 getting a proof of §19.\n"
"\n"
"You can then use §20 to close the goal"
