#: Game.Doc.tactic_doc
msgid "The §0 tactic allows you to add theorems to the context (which you would have to prove, of course).\n"
"\n"
"## One step\n"
"If the proof is one step, then the following:\n"
"§1\n"
"will do, where §2 with §3, i.e. §4 is a proof of §5\n"
"\n"
"The result would be adding the following to the hypothesis:\n"
"§6\n"
"\n"
"You are storing the proof of §7 in §8 so that you don't have to construct this proof everytime you need it.\n"
"\n"
"## Multiple steps\n"
"If the proof is multiple steps, then:\n"
"§9\n"
"will change the current goal to §10 which is what you want to prove.\n"
"\n"
"After being proven, the original goal is restored with §11 added (which is a proof of the proposition §12)\n"
"\n"
"### Example\n"
"§13\n"
"will change the goal to §14, which after proving would restore the original goal with the theorem §15 added and ready to be used."
msgstr ""

#. §0: ```
#. Assumptions:
#. h : A = B
#. 
#. Goal:
#. some expression involving A
#. ```
