#. §13: `=`
#. §14: `↔`
#. §15: `rw [h]`
#. §16: `h : x=2`
#. §17: `h : P ↔ Q`
#: Game.Doc.tactic_doc
msgid "Given the following:\n"
"§0\n"
"\n"
"§1 would change the goal by replacing every occurrence of §2 with §3.\n"
"\n"
"Moreover §4 would apply the rewrite on an assumption §5 instead of the goal.\n"
"\n"
"By default, rw uses an equation in the forward direction, matching the left-hand side of the equation §6 with an occurrence of §7 in the goal, and replaces it with the right-hand side, i.e. §8.\n"
"\n"
"The notation §9 can be used to instruct the tactic to use the equality §10 in the reverse direction, i.e. replace an occurrence of §11 with §12.\n"
"\n"
"## Behavior with §13 and §14\n"
"For §15, the behavior is exactly the same for both, whether you had §16 or §17."
msgstr ""

