#: Game.Doc.doc
msgid "## Objects\n"
"\n"
"The objects involved are:\n"
"- of type inhabitant indicated by a capital letter\n"
"- the two finite sets §0, §1.\n"
"\n"
"As a proof state:\n"
"§2\n"
"There will be at most three inhabitants in the puzzles for simplicity, but you can ofcourse have more.\n"
"\n"
"## Assumptions\n"
"Knights tell the true and knaves lie. So no one can be both at the same time, i.e. §3\n"
"\n"
"Moreover, every inhabitant is either a knight or a knave, i.e. §4 for any §5.\n"
"\n"
"As a proof state:\n"
"§6\n"
"\n"
"## Summary\n"
"Putting every together:\n"
"§7\n"
"\n"
"## Translating statements to formal notation\n"
"Given an inhabitant §8,\n"
"\n"
"The translation we use is based on the following:\n"
"- If §9 is a knight, then §10's statement is true.\n"
"- If §11's statement is true, then §12 is telling the truth, i.e. is a knight.\n"
"\n"
"Formally:\n"
"§13\n"
"where §14 represents §15's statement.\n"
"\n"
"Combining them we get,\n"
"§16\n"
"\n"
"### Quick Example\n"
"If,\n"
"§17\n"
"\n"
"then,\n"
"§18\n"
"\n"
"Combining them using §19:\n"
"§20\n"
"\n"
"### Equivalent translations, using knaves\n"
"Given inhabitant §21,\n"
"\n"
"The translation we use is based on the following:\n"
"- If §22 is a knave, then §23's statement is false, i.e. its negation is true.\n"
"- If §24's statement is false, then §25 is lying, i.e. is a knave.\n"
"\n"
"Formally:\n"
"§26\n"
"where §27 represents §28's statement.\n"
"\n"
"Combining them we get,\n"
"§29\n"
"\n"
"### Quick Example\n"
"If,\n"
"§30\n"
"\n"
"then,\n"
"§31\n"
"\n"
"Combining them using §32:\n"
"§33"
msgstr ""

