#: Game.Doc.doc
msgid "Logical implication §0 is made up of two components:\n"
"- The premise, which in this case is §1\n"
"- The conclusion, which in this case is §2\n"
"\n"
"§3 is read as 'If P is true, then Q is true.\n"
"\n"
"# Truth table\n"
"§4\n"
"\n"
"A statement §5 is false when §6 is true and §7 false, it's true otherwise.\n"
"\n"
"# Implication as a function\n"
"What logical implication does is that it takes evidence or proof for §8 and transforms it returning a proof of §9.\n"
"The truth of §10 IMPLIES the truth of §11. A proof of §12 IMPLIES a proof of §13.\n"
"\n"
"In other words, it acts like a function. If you give §14 a proof of §15, you get a proof of §16.\n"
"\n"
"§17 acts like a function. It takes a proof of §18 and returns a proof of §19.\n"
"\n"
"Given §20 §21, §22 is a proof of Q"
msgstr ""

